description: 1
name: Le journal de Spider-Man

description: This is the end! The end of the series and the end of the world if Doctor Ment, Harry and Elvis the Airpuff doesn't stop The Great Cthulhu and his evil army of evilness! But they are not alone! They have the help of Selma, Otis the Zombi, the Stinker Pirate and his ghost ship. Cthulhu Mythos and fun? Yes, it's possible!
name: The Curse of the Mottled Tentacle Part III

description: With Batman and Robin about to be turned into pasta by General Gumm's elaborate death trap, the Green Hornet and Kato hunt Gumm and the Joker on their own.
name: Chapter Nine

description: The rascally raccoon returns along with heaps of Halloween hijinks. All that and the final showdown with the menace known as Rabbit. This one is not to be missed.

Flashback to the beginning... Wrong place, wrong time.

Hitsohi remembers the twist of fate that triggered his quest for vengeance.

Is this the birth of a TRUE MONSTER?
name: Chapter 2

description:
The rogue breaker, Skarra Boc, finally catches up with Justice at Dreamers Vale and she's planning on making things personal... if she gets the chance.

Justice will prevail but at what cost? Her past comes back to haunt her, as those things usually tend to do.

Why are you reading this? The comic is much more interesting and has all this stuff in it.

In Issue 2 of Fates Abound the story of Ryan Altair continues as he unravels his self-made destiny. He encounters the artistic genius of Lavinia Fontana, the leading artist of a full immersion virtual reality startup company called Immersa Flix. The NYC cyber crimes division is also hot on the heels of Ryan's suspicious financial activities as he squanders millions in lottery winnings. Will he continue down this destructive path or will it take an encounter with inter dimensional intelligences to set him on the right course.
name: Observation

description:
Playing With Fire

A political protest! An impatient lady! A crispy cook! And a child in need! Fearless Man is playing with fire and the consequences could be dire!
name: Playing With Fire

description:
Inspired by Tales From the Crypt, Twilight Zone, and Creep Show, Zenescope goes back to its roots of horror as the publisher known for re-inventing classics delves into an entirely new bag of tricks.

When a college undergrad decides to stay in and study, she will find that another seemingly inconsequential decision she makes will have a lasting effect on her.

List of covers and their creators:

CoverNameCreator(s)Sidebar Location

BCover BEric J & Luis Guerrero2
CCover CJorge Meguro3
REMontreal Comic Con Exclusive Cover, Limited to 500Jose Luis & Ula Mos

Note: The digital edition (9/10/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Dont Turn On the Lights

description:
Who's The Boss... Hog?

In post-apocalyptic Canada, guns don't kill people - slapshots do.

For the mutated tribes trying to survive nuclear winter - which is like normal Canadian winter, just more radioactive - hockey serves as a form of ritual warfare in which communities gamble their resources on the abilities of their squad to score goals and bust heads on the ice.

With team captain Skully injured, manager Lizzy must step into his skates and lead the Edmonton Atomics - Squid, Stretch, and Ugly Dave - against a new threat from the north: Boss Hog and his Rig Pigs. In her first game since the end of the world, Lizzy must line up across from an abrasive, refrigerator-sized pig-man... so that should go smoothly.
name: Who's The Boss... Hog?

description: Haunted by dreams of demonic destruction, the band attempts to make sense of what happened Saturday night at The Descent. It's a trial by fire when they're forced to learn how to use their new found abilities when the source of their nightmares shows up looking for a fight.
The K-141 Kursk Russian Nuclear Submarine has sank in the Barents Sea. A frantic rescue begins.
name: Chapter 2

description: In "I...Batman," there's a new face of crimefighting in Gotham City, but will this twisted creation do more harm than good? Next, a serial killer targets random citizens of Gotham for a fiery death, and the Dark Knight detects a pattern the police didn't in "Ashes to Ashes." Finally, in "Herded Limits," when the Dark Knight foils the Riddler's latest plot, Dr. Chase Meridian presents evidence that Edward Nigma isn't clinically insane after all!

volume.name: Legends of the Dark Knight 100-Page Super Spectacular

description: No secrets are left in hiding. No past pain left unfelt. Everything that came before is explained by the explosive revelation contained in this final chapter of this groundshaking series.

The Voyage into Darkness

Terror and a friendly ally await our team when they search underground for their missing leader.
name: The Voyage into Darkness

volume.name: THE NANOC.A.M.P. (Cosmic Adventure of Maximum Potential)

description:
The Masters of Spinjitzu are stuck on a comet, having traveled through space to save the World of Ninjago from the Nindroids. As they race through the stars, it becomes apparent that they are not alone on the comet. Something has stowed away Something not of their world

Note: The digital edition (9/10/2014) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Comet Crisis

description:
The Rise of Raccoonicorn

Noah's plan for a post flood utopia populated with his hand picked followers was ruined when his little brother Leon showed up with his own ark filled with all of the weird leftover creatures that were supposed to have drowned.

But now Noah has been kidnapped by the mysterious villian, Raccoonicorn and it's up to Leon, Squatch and Choop to find and rescue him. The first thing standing in their way is the tough as nails leader of the Noah's Ark Police Department , Chief Bunny.
name: The Rise of Raccoonicorn

description:
Pewfell is a slacker wizard who lives in the fabulous city of Spirekassle. He's married to Tina the Warrior Princess and is landlord to a small blue gnome who hates him.

In this episode, Pewfell is kicked out of his house by a gang of feminist gnomes and seeks refuge in the arms of a brainwashing cult. Presented in full color.

We learn the dark truth behind Heinrich and Rebecca's relationship on Earth, while on Resurrection Requiem's dreams are haunted by Lamias, the victims of his cruelties on Earth. As Mortis continues to plot against him, Requiem discovers dangerous information about his past that he must keep hidden at all cost. But Rebecca has a new secret weapon in her war against the Vampires, the religious maniac, Torquemada...
name: Dracula

description: Wonder Woman faces her greatest peril as the Gods gifts are withdrawn one by one. And since their first gift was life, how far will her unraveling go?
name: Taketh Away, Part 1 of 2

description: The devastating, action packed conclusion to Torn! Will The Wolf survive? Does he even want to?

Toxic Wastoid

Stunt Superstar Trip Fantastic is on the run, Trying to piece together a mystery while being pursued in every direction by a growing list of enemies.
name: Toxic Wastoid

description:
Lost Dogs

Mao discovers that the mysterious shadow figures he absorbed grant him near immortality. But he must still face the judgement of the Council of Elders for his failure to complete the mission, and plead for the council to rescue Nora. Meanwhile Dezmin prepares to settle into a new life in the small town, but a mysterious figure from his past has tracked him down.
name: Lost Dogs

description:
Last Stand of the Dark Witch

Tina and Gina face off against the Dark Witch hoping to rescue their father, while Haslow Falls' police force turns the tide against the growing Darkness.
name: Last Stand of the Dark Witch

description:
Book 2

Yani begins to tell the story of how she descended into madness and came back alive and well. In this issue, she talks about her job teaching at a local school and how she was distracted by her obsession with her ex-boyfriend.
name: Book 2

description: As Yuki continues to flirt with rebellion, things take a violent turn when fuzzy vengeance descends upon her.
name: The Confrontation!

description:
Blood and Honour

Our hero's undead viking concerns get overshadowed by the arrival of a much bigger problem! PLUS: Darius and Daphne must each face the decisions of their lives... While Detective Marko Killigan is forced to reveal his greatest secret.
name: Blood and Honour

description: Billy is a 9 year old Space Captain, he's billions of miles away from Earth, and he's about to miss the bus on the first day of 4th grade. Will he make it back in time? Find out in the exciting first issue of "The Adventures of a 4th Grade Space Captain!"

volume.name: The Adventures of a 4th Grade Space Captain

description: The future Brotherhood of Evil Mutants, last seen in "Battle of the Atom," is back - and they're still gunning for yesterday's X-Men! But even as the Brotherhood takes its next devastating step against the time-tossed teens, the mysteries surrounding Jean Grey begin to unfold! Jean came back from her Shi'ar trial...different. What does this mean for her future, for the past of the woman she's supposed to become and for the rest of the X-Men? Past, present and future collide when the Future Brotherhood exacts its final judgment on the All-New X-Men! And it's mutant magic as only Mighty Marvel could do it as artist Stuart Immonen is joined by a practical hall of fame lineup of comic-book artists! Collecting ALL-NEW X-MEN #25-29.
name: Volume 5

description:
The Boy and the Beast

A young monster hunter in the American Old West seeks to get his first kill with the help of his mentor, Vlad Tepes.
name: The Boy and the Beast

description:
Fresh off the biggest bomb in Hollywood history, producer Nathan T. Rex enters a downward spiral of drugs and depravity in a quest to resurrect his career and save his soul. Over budget and behind schedule on PRESIDENTS DAY, he is backed into a corner by bad publicity, a crap project, and studio politics. But enlisting serial-killer-turned-murder-consultant Darwin, his trusty assistant Igor, narcotics from Doctor Love, and the lovely actress Coconut, T. Rex will stop at nothing in his quest for cinematic fame and glory. God help us all.

Note: The digital edition (9/10/2014) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Book One

description:
Blank Slater wants to find his place. But to do that, first, he must find his face.

"Blank Slater, The Boy With The Dry-Erase Face" is a story of emotional connectivity and creative expression written for young readers, early listeners, and the parents and teachers of both. Created by Matt Bergin and illustrated by Zach Wideman, this full-color picture book explores common but complicated ideas -- emotional confusion; the quest for tolerance and acceptance in a sometimes cruel world; practice making perfect, but only given time -- through a simple, sweet tale of blank-faced boy meeting wild-eyed girl. The print edition includes activity pages that allow readers to explore the book's themes further when the story is over.

volume.name: Blank Slater, The Boy With The Dry-Erase Face

description:
Teen pop idol Mizuki Asoh has a secret that only his management knows. He's actually not a teen at all, but a grown man with a youthful face and body who is the father of a teenage boy. How this all came to pass is revealed as his son matures and searches for a sense of identity. Is this deception all the selfish ploy of an egocentric man, or is there some other reason at play? Growing up is hard, but so is parenting, and perhaps unconditional love is before them both, unseen...

Chapter Titles

  • Stage 1: Sana Fujisaki
  • Stage 2: Shinobu Sendoh
  • Stage 3: Shinobu Sendoh
  • Stage 4: Shiho Izumi
  • Stage 5: Mizuki Asoh
  • Stage 6: Mizuki Asoh
  • Stage 7: Mizuki Asoh
  • Stage 8: Naoki Fujisaki
  • Middle Age Revolution -Child Rearing-
name: Vol. 1

description: The moment she first saw her best friend's fiance, Tom, Sylvie could feel her heart rate rising. She quells those feelings and focuses on preparing her friend's wedding as the professional event planner that she is, but then the bride disappears right before the wedding! Sylvie ends up spending a passionate night with Tom, to comfort him during his time of loss. She then sends him a letter telling him that she's pregnant with his child, but when she doesn't hear back from him, Sylvie feels betrayed and unwanted. What are the chances that they'd be reunited by a magazine project to design her "dream wedding," which lands her in the role of the bride and him as the groom?
name: Vol. 1

description: Molly is depressed. Her brother and his wife have invited her to spend the Christmas holiday with them, but when she arrives at their home, she learns she will also be spending it with the last man she ever wanted to see, Gideon. They had met three years ago, a chance encounter at the house of Gideon's brother. Seeing Molly in a disgraceful mess, Gideon assumed she was his brother's mistress, and he's hated her ever since. Completely unaware of their history, Molly's brother and sister-in-law try to play cupid to the two of them. All Molly can do is sigh.
name: Vol. 1

description:
Remastered and Colored!

Dalrak finds a sword, rescues a person or two, and has a few fights. Originally written and illustrated in just 36 hours, this issue has been re-drawn re-lettered and colored! So come see the origin of Dalrak The Mighty in his debut issue!

Something awaits inside the ball room of The Dolridge House and it's becoming impatient. A traveler has come to tip the fragile balance Father Dolridge has tried so hard to maintain and The Witness is tired of waiting for his debt to be paid. But someone else is stalking Father Dolridge from the shadows and it may be something closer and far more insidious than any demon.
name: TPB

description:
Starlet Lost - Pt 1

Silent film starlet, Zia, has gone missing before completing her first talkie. Now Silver Screen Studios has hired a cocky Private Investigator named Niles Lance to find Zia. As Niles learns about Zia he discovers her disappearance is far from ordinary.
name: Starlet Lost - Pt 1

description:
Over the course of the six years that would come to be known as the "The Era of Great Wonders," or the "Time of Giant Men," the people of Pangaea lived in the shadow of giant monsters that waged war across their homeland.

As word of the first giant monster attacks reached them, they found themselves struggling to make sense of a world that would never be the same again. In the days ahead that struggle would become one simply to survive in the wake of the massive destruction and loss of life caused by the attacks.

This in their story in their own words...

In 1961, Stan Lee and Jack Kirby lit the fuse of the greatest revolution in comic-book history - the Marvel Age of Comics - and it started right here, in the pages of FANTASTIC FOUR! With the space race on, Reed Richards, Ben Grimm, Sue Storm and Johnny Storm shoot for the stars - but after their craft is bombarded by cosmic rays, they return to Earth with the startling powers of the Fantastic Four! These weren't just any super heroes, though - the Fantastic Four were a realistic, relatable, bickering and loveable family that couldn't pay their rent and didn't always love their powers. So crack open this Epic Collection and enjoy the beginning of the series that earned the name 'The World's Greatest Comic Magazine!' Collecting FANTASTIC FOUR (1961) #1-18.
name: TPB

volume.name: Fantastic Four Epic Collection: The World's Greatest Comic Magazine

description:
Back after much critical acclaim! It's the collected editions of Freestyle! The comic no-one thought would make it past the first issue! Created by Australian Mark Pursell who likes to think he can draw and write and stuff and occasionally can, Freestyle is a comic. It is funny and has words and pretty pictures!

Freestyle #1

Tales Of Rawr/Aww

In this issue Stupid Cat forgets an anniversary. Cactus smashes a car through a wall. Stupid Cat is sent to the doghouse. Cops arrest Stupid Cat and Cactus on suspicion of nothing. Nothing because it's all a clever ruse by the evil Chloe to destroy them all! Oh, and there is zombies in it too.

Freestyle #2

Tales Of Erk/ Oh!

More stuff happens in this issue! Chloe ramps up her plans to destroy Stupid and the gang by using her hoards of Fake Cops, Copters and bitchiness. Sox also gets a bad case of the fleas and potentially ruins everyone's plans.

Freestyle #3

Tales of Rawr 2/ United

In this issue the poop hits the fan royally! Will the good guys win? Will they not win? Do they get bored and go out for slushies?! Find out in the thrilling conclusion to this particular story!
name: Vol. 1

description: Nick Drnaso uses lush colors with a deadline to tell a stranger than life story of some people picking up trash off the side of the road.

Contains the story Seaside Home which was nominated for an 2014 Eisner award in the category for Best Short Story.

Oily Comics is proud to present a new anthology comic from Josh Simmons, Wendy Chin, Karn Piana, and The Partridge in the Pear Tree. Habit features five stories designed to test the limits of good taste.

"I want you to pretend to be my lover." At the request of her lovable friend, the old millionaire Kastro, Joanna arrives in Greece to play the part of a wicked woman who deceives the elderly. Sure enough, the Kastro residence is in an uproar over the young lover the sixty-seven-year-old head of the family has brought with him. But a fated meeting awaits her there. It is with old Kastro's son, Demetrios. Each time she is shot through with his glances of intermingling hostility and jealousy, her body and heart are shaken. But in their positions as a father's lover and his son, they cannot possibly be drawn together?
name: Vol. 1

description: For the first time the cult favorite series is together at last! From the next generation of characters that have made Bluewater famous comes the most infamous of them all. Take youthful energy. Add in some over-active imagination. Mix in some powdered donuts. Sprinkle it with delusional disorder and you get... Insane Jane, The kookiest action hero of the 21st century! Will Jane save the day? Will Jane destroy the world? Will she remember to take her medication? Also included is the 10th Muse full issue featuring a cover by Roger Cruz that was the inspirtaion for the series. Over 200 pages of crazy!
name: TPB

description:
How Sharper Than a Dragon's Tooth Part One of Six

John Aman and the mysterious Dr. Vampire are routing a nest of the undead when Sylvia Manners, operations chief for the X-Bureau --a shadowy government agency that monitors super-human activity, arrives with bad news. Zoe Henderson - investigative reporter and Aman's close friend - has gone missing. Zoe's last known whereabouts were at the controversial bio-weapons lab known as Googer Industries.
name: How Sharper Than A Dragon's Tooth Part One of Six

description: Collected for the first time. from the best selling novelist John Saul, comes "God Project". Eastbury, Mass. Quiet, peaceful, prosperous. Surely the ideal place to raise a family? For the Montgomery family, the death of their baby daughter is a mystery that medicine should be able to answer, but can't. For the Corliss family, the disappearance of their teenage son will bring many eyes to Eastbury, and spark a quite different type of mystery. What has happened to these children? Eastbury happened.
name: TPB

description:
Sex, Drugs, and Alien Possession

Izzy Montoya -- college student, disaffected, and possibly insane. She dreams of another life on Mars. Features the first three chapters of The Girl from Mars, plus The Galilean!
name: Sex, Drugs, and Alien Possession

description:
The End / The Beginning

Metaphysical Neuroma is a bizarre tale that begins in the mind of an amnesiac who is flickering on the brink between life and death; he just happens to be the greatest hero in all of time and space.

Join him as he must soon re-discover the epic end-boss that earned him the title, and the round 2 fight he must this time win to save the universe again!
name: The End / The Beginning

description: A collection of 11 short stories from award-winning writer Gary Reed. Pulled from various sources over his career writing for Caliber Comics, Transfuzion, Image, and IDW Publishing - these are standalone short tales. He is joined by some of today's popular comic artists to bring his tales of horror, suspense, often times with a literary bent to life for the reader.
name: Vol. 1

description:
Okita Souji was once the finest swordsmen of his generation. Once.

Today, he struggles; with the tuberculosis that will claim his life, and with some unresolved business from his time in the Shinsengumi, the Shogun's infamous counter-terrorism unit.

Alice Cooper is a man, a band, and an idea that took on a life of its own, a voice for shock and glitter rockers whose influence created stars like Marilyn Manson and KISS. Behind the paint, the boa constrictors, and the staged executions is a man whose creative energies gave rise to a legend. Half truth, half fiction, Alice Cooper defines fame.

Years have passed since the Nome King has wrested power from Ozma, the rightful Queen of Oz. When the earthly trio managed to break the evil spell of Witch Mombi on Scarecrow, Tin Man, and Lion, a band of heroes join together to retake the Emerald City. Join Tik-Tok, Wogglebug, Jack Pumpkinhead, Sawhorse, and other heroes of Oz as they embark on a war to save the very heart and soul of Oz. Based on the series of novels by Frank L. Baum with a decidedly modern twist. Collects issues 6-10 of the OZ series.
name: Volume 2

description:
Start-up companies live on the forefront of innovation. However, these brilliant scientists and engineers, renowned for uncovering knowledge to transform humanity and change society, find their scientific efforts spoiled by competitors or herculean heroes, claiming to be acting in the best interest of society.

This barrier to innovation led teams of enterprising scientists to plot their revenge in secret projects. They scheme to find the key to universal domination, and in this mad bid for power, an old scientist named Paracelsus and his project seek out scientists who have made critical discoveries in the technology that will allow them to rule over all:

The Time Machine.
name: The Maddening of Doctor Rewrite

description:
Peace Machine

In the 1970s, a bold plan was taken to create an autonomous soldier that could operate within the difficult strain of war. Fast forward to 1979, and a prototype called TBD-079 is built in the advanced weapons research facility known as Area 51. Guy Ayumu (last name pronounced eye-u-moo), a well respected computer scientist and engineer substituted the military artificial intelligence (AI) program for an AI of his own creation. With the prototype's body and Guy Ayumu's expertly built AI, the result is the dawn of a technological revolution for humanity.

At what cost...? Even though the purpose of an autonomous soldier is to focus strictly on enemy targets, does that guarantee machines will? No matter how well intended Guy Ayumu and his team guide TBD-089 to prepare for war situations, there is a mind present and soon enough TBD-089 begins to use it.

Pretentious Record Store Guy is a three issue miniseries written and illustrated by Carlos Gabriel Ruiz about a guy who works in a record store, goes to all of the coolest shows, and knows about all the new, up-and-coming bands before you do. While his life is made in the shade, his hair is epic, and his record collection is worth a small fortune (in some circles), he realizes that he's been coasting for far too long and that life is passing him by. What does he do?

He decides that life won't wait, and if he wants to make his dreams come true, then he needs to be the one to make it happen.
name: Mondo Digital LP

description: Helena marries the man she's always adored, the viscount Carleton. But her husband believes that their matrimony was all so that she could gain his fortune and he refuses to open his heart to her. He even goes so far as to declare that her son is no child of his and goes off to war, only to go missing. Everything after that is a living hell for Helena. Her husband's family treats her like a hussy, cuts her off. But seven years later, while she's been diligently raising her son, her husband suddenly shows up, ragged and on the verge of collapsing!
name: Vol. 1

description:
Scarlet Huntress Tales Through Time is an anthology featuring 3 new stories of Scarlet's battles with with werewolves and other cryptids.

John Barker weaves a tale in "The Hollow" were Scarlet comes across a surprising new enemy.

Bryan K. Borgman tells a story of Scarlet in 2015 as a member of the Special Missions Force tracking down a pack of wolves in Detroit in the story "Enter the Huntress."

Stephanie Forney continues the story from issue 2 as Scarlet discovers more from her past in "Search for Answers"
name: Tales Through Time

description: Determined to save her family's company from ruin, Tamsin agrees to become a bride to the wealthy shiekh tycoon Aziz. But on the day of their marriage, the wedding party is suddenly attacked by bandits. After being drugged and knocked unconscious, Tamsin wakes up to the sight of a handsome, mysterious man who tells her, "I've waited my entire life to exact my revenge of destroying your fianc? and your family!" before stealing a kiss from Tamsin! But who knew that a kidnapper's kiss could be so hot and so arousing?
name: Vol. 1
